<subSubSection id="C33A6522FFEB293BF889FA3E09144802" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEB293BF889FA3E0CC849BA" blockId="5.[151,1437,1224,2043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF889FA3E0DC24A9A" bold="true" box="[199,462,1476,1502]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is easily distinguished from its congeners by the leaf margin-shaped longitudinal ridges on trunk. The margins of these longitudinal ridges are slightly expanded, lobed, sinuate, and sometimes bluntly pointed. Even though the trunk of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BFABFF9F60FC54962" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[753,969,1548,1574]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="haejooni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BFABFF9F60FC54962" box="[753,969,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Philodina haejooni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEB293BFB9FF9F708014963" box="[977,1037,1549,1575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is lightly granulated, the lobed and sinuate parts of the longitudinal ridges are not from the compaction of the granules on trunk, but from the slight expansion of the margins. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BFA0AF9AE0EBE492A" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1830" box="[580,690,1620,1646]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BFA0AF9AE0EBE492A" box="[580,690,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Philodina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has several species/subspecies with highly granulated trunk such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BF8F6F9830D4949D6" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2019" box="[184,325,1657,1682]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="corrugata">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF8F6F9830D4949D6" box="[184,325,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. corrugata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BF91BF9830EBD49D6" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2020" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2020" box="[341,689,1656,1683]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF91BF9830DDE49D6" box="[341,466,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. clypeata</emphasis>
Song &amp; Lee, 2020
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BFAF0F983081849D6" authority="rugosa Bryce, 1903" authorityName="Bryce" authorityYear="1903" box="[702,1044,1656,1683]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" species="rugosa" subSpecies="rugosa">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BFAF0F9830F8D49D6" box="[702,897,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. rugosa rugosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B58FFEB293BFBC7F983081849D6" author="Bryce, D." box="[905,1044,1656,1683]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="523 - 530" refId="ref5969" refString="Bryce, D. (1903) On two new species of Philodina. Journal of the Quekett Microscopical Club, Series 2, 8, 523 - 530." type="journal article" year="1903">Bryce, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and its two other subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BFD3EF9830D8049F2" authority="Bryce, 1903" authorityName="Bryce" authorityYear="1903" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" species="rugosa" subSpecies="coriacea">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BFD3EF9830CF549F2" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. r. coriacea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B58FFEB293BF94CF9670D8049F2" author="Bryce, D." box="[258,396,1692,1719]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="523 - 530" refId="ref5969" refString="Bryce, D. (1903) On two new species of Philodina. Journal of the Quekett Microscopical Club, Series 2, 8, 523 - 530." type="journal article" year="1903">Bryce, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BF988F9670EEE49F2" authority="Bryce, 1903" authorityName="Bryce" authorityYear="1903" box="[454,738,1692,1719]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="callosa">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF988F9670E4049F2" box="[454,588,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. r. callosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B58FFEB293BFA1BF9670EEE49F2" author="Bryce, D." box="[597,738,1692,1719]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="523 - 530" refId="ref5969" refString="Bryce, D. (1903) On two new species of Philodina. Journal of the Quekett Microscopical Club, Series 2, 8, 523 - 530." type="journal article" year="1903">Bryce, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BFAA1F9670FE349F2" authority="Milne, 1916" authorityName="Milne" authorityYear="1916" box="[751,1007,1692,1718]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="scabra">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BFAA1F9670F5449F2" box="[751,856,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. scabra</emphasis>
Milne, 1916
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BFC63F967099549F2" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2020" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2020" box="[1069,1433,1692,1719]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BFC63F96708B649F2" box="[1069,1210,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. verrucosa</emphasis>
Song &amp; Lee, 2020
</taxonomicName>
. None of these 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BF970F93A0E0A499E" box="[318,518,1728,1754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF970F93A0DA0499E" box="[318,428,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Philodina</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
has leaf margin-shaped longitudinal ridges on trunk like those 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFEB293BFC99F93B095A499E" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[1239,1366,1728,1754]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="haejooni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BFC99F93B095A499E" box="[1239,1366,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">P. haejooni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFEB293BFD11F93B0990499F" box="[1375,1436,1729,1755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEB293BF889F8F209144802" blockId="5.[151,1437,1224,2043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">The other important diagnostic characteristics of this new species include the lateral expansions of cingulum as well as the extended lateral folds on each side of the pseudosegment bearing dorsal antenna in feeding.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A6522FFEB2939F889F8AA0E6A4D79" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="406" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFEB2939F889F8AA0E674EE9" blockId="5.[151,1437,1224,2043]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="406" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFEB293BF889F8AA0D55482E" bold="true" box="[199,345,1872,1898]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Description.</emphasis>
No eyespots. Body lightly granulated. Rostral lamella bilobed and very short; narrower than rostrum width; with tufts of cilia posterolaterally. Rostrum round and slightly shorter than its width. Corona wider than cingulum; the ratio of corona width to cingulum width about 1.12: 1–1.13: 1. Sulcus as wide as pedicel width. Upper lip arched and bilobed medially; as high as sulcus base; much lower than trochal discs. Cingulum extended laterally; each extension short and round laterally; cingulum slightly wider than cingulum pad; the ratio of cingulum width to cingulum pad width about 1.10: 1–1.11: 1. Antenna short. Two extended lateral folds on either side of pseudosegment bearing antenna in feeding. Teeth 3/3. Pharyngeal tube much shorter than trophi length. Longitudinal ridge on trunk slightly expanded and leaf margin-shaped; margins lobed, sinuate, and sometimes bluntly pointed. Rump gradually tapering to foot; preanal pseudosegment plump posteriorly; anal pseudosegment round medially. Foot very short and with four pseudosegments; the ratio of total body length in creeping to foot length about 8.4: 1. Spurs long, finger-shaped, thin and with wide interspace; slightly plump medially; lateral margins of spurs tapering to dull and knobbed ends; interspace width slightly wider than spur length; the ratio of interspace width to spur length about 1.3: 1. Egg oval and with smooth surface.
</paragraph>
